<p>

An update to the Steam client and HLDS update tool has just been released. Steam will update itself automatically when you restart. Here is a list of the changes:<br/><br/><ul style="padding-bottom: 0px; margin-bottom: 0px;"><b>STEAM CLIENT CHANGES / ADDITIONS:</b><br/><li> Steam will now generate a receipt when you purchase a product, instead of sending it via e-mail<br/><li>Removed email verification<br/><li> All Steam error messages are now localized<br/><li>Improved offline behavior if no SteamUI.dll or Steam.dll present<br/><li>Improved content server responsiveness<br/><li>Disabled background preloaders when any game is running<br/><li>Preloader checks to see if an item will fit in the cache (improves going offline)<br/><li>Improved behavior of content "tickets" (thrown out if system clock more than 4 weeks off)<br/><li>Improved loading progress bar time calculation<br/><li>Improved startup speed of Steam <br/><li>Improved responsiveness of user cancel<br/><li>Changed legal characters in new account names to only be 'a'-'z', 'A'-'Z', '0'-'9', and '_'<br/><br/><b>HLDS UPDATE TOOL CHANGES / ADDITIONS:</b><br/><li>Added "-retry" flag -- auto-retry to get content every 30 seconds<br/></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></li></ul><br/></p>
